<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.184390>
    bibo:endPage "68" ;
    bibo:journal "Zootaxa" ;
    bibo:startPage "59" ;
    bibo:volume "1894" ;
    dc:creator "Oliver, Paul; Tjaturadi, Burhan; Krey, Keliopas; Richards, Stephen" ;
    dc:date "2008" ;
    dc:title "A new species of large Cyrtodactylus (Squamata: Gekkonidae) from Melanesia" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.184393>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.184394>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.184395> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.184393>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Photos in life of the two similar species of large bodied Cyrtodactylus known from the Raja Ampat archipelago A) Cyrtodactylus zugi sp. nov. (paratype; MZB lace 5575) and B) Cyrtodactylus irianjayaensis (MZB lace 5765), from Salawati Island. Note the darker bands, strongly defined nuchal stripe and patterned dorsal surface of head on C. zugi sp. nov. Photographs S. Richards." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/184393/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.184394>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Known distribution of Cyrtodactylus zugi sp. nov. (circle) and Cyrtodactylus irianjayaensis (triangle) in Papua Barat, Indonesia." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/184394/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.184395>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Large fig tree in disturbed rainforest at the type locality of Cyrtodactylus zugi sp. nov on the southern coast of Batanta Island, Papua Barat, Indonesia. Both the holotype (MZB lace 5574) and one paratype (MZB lace 5575) were collected from the lower trunk of this tree on the same night. Photograph S. Richards." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/184395/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

